    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `z=` isn't able to give suggestion. Like pressing it on empty line, whitespace and etc. It changes `nospell` to `spell`. But using it on word doesn't affect `nospell`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nospell` changed\n```bash\nnvim --clean\n:set spell? # nospell\nz=\n:set spell? #   spell\n```\n- `nospell` didn't changed\n```bash\nnvim --clean\n:set spell? # nospell\ni\nasd\nESC\nz=\n1\nENTER\n:set spell? # nospell\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nospell` remain `nospell`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0 commit 18c5f06c9f6068b9a26a1ed4ab0f66b91db85cd9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim v9.2.0068\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKDE neon User Edition x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
